This paper discusses reputation management in the context of Internet of Vehicles, which is a subfield of computer networks and communication (cs.NI). The paper also applies evolutionary game theory to model the evolution process of malicious users' attacking strategies, which falls under game theory (cs.GT). The paper also discusses the methodology of evaluation simulations, which could be categorized under security and privacy (cs.CR) or control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper applies a reputation management scheme with multiple utility functions, which could be related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
